The Digital Talent Management Platform was designed to simplify employee management, performance tracking, and communication within organizations. 
Through research and analysis, key challenges were identified, such as difficulty in monitoring employee progress, 
lack of centralized systems, and inefficient communication between Employees, Managers, and Admins. 
To address these issues, a user-centered solution was created with role-based dashboards that allow employees to manage tasks and track progress, 
managers to assign work and monitor performance, and admins to control overall system operations. 
The platform focuses on providing a clean, intuitive interface to ensure ease of use and improved productivity.

The design process included research, user personas, wireframing, high-fidelity UI design, and interactive prototyping using Figma.
Usability validation was conducted to refine the user experience and ensure smooth navigation across all screens. 
Key features such as task management, performance tracking, notifications, and centralized communication were incorporated to enhance functionality.
This project helped in gaining practical experience in end-to-end UX design, improving skills in problem-solving, user research, 
and creating efficient, user-friendly digital solutions.

